						               													<description>(Loosely translated from the instructions:)  Dungeon Hazard.  After a cataclysm, the world has become one massive dungeon.  In this Dungeon World many species fight for survival.  Make You Fortress is a 2-player [abstract] game, where opponents fight over control of a Dungeon Kingdom, in the same world as Make You Conquest (aka Dungeon War).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents:&amp;#10;Board&amp;#10;11 blue men &amp;amp; 11 red Men&amp;#10;10 cards&amp;#10;instructions&amp;#10;&amp;#10;User summary:  This is a tile laying game, with a card playing option.  Players will take turns laying their wood counters on one of the 4x4 grid (16 board spaces).  When you have a strength advantage in a row or column, you can push your opponent off the board and out of the fortress.  The player who loses 3 characters first is defeated.  The optional cards add a greater element of risk by allowing a player to sacrifice a character counter in exchange for a random card.  A card may give a player the edge needed to win the game, or it may yield nothing at all.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
